 Here's a LaTeX code snippet that generates a sine function plot using pgfplots package with the specified specifications:

```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{pgfplots}

\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\begin{axis}[
    xmin=-2.1, xmax=2.1, xtick={-2., -1.9, ..., 1.9, 2.}, xticklabels={$-\pi$, $-2\pi+\frac{\pi}{2}$,..., $2\pi-\frac{\pi}{2}$, $\pi$},
    xlabel=$x$, ylabel=$sin(x)$,
    grid=major,
    axis lines=middle,
    legend columns=1,
    width=\textwidth, height=0.4\textwidth,
    domain=-2*pi:2*pi, samples=51,
    cycle list name=black white, every mark/.append code={fill=white},
]
\addplot[smooth,blue,line width=1.5pt] {sin(deg(\x));};
\end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}%

% [title] \label{fig:sine_function} % Replace this comment with your title and label
\end{document}
```

